efficiency: HIGH  
time complexity: O(k * 2^n)  
space complexity: O(n)  
energy implications: LOW  
explanation: The solution uses depth-first search to try all possible combinations of numbers to form k subsets with equal sums. It first checks if the total sum of the array can be divided by k, and if the largest number is not greater than the target sum. The dfs function is used to recursively try different numbers to form the subsets.

